This is not done in the proper way - as I mentioned before you can reduce page initialisation, click() and isExpectedPage() just to one line.

When you do this the way I mentioned:

final ConfigStudioPage csp = pp.getConfigStudioMenuItem().click(ConfigStudioPage.class));

you can skip isExpectedPage() method as we already have checked if page is correct in click(ExpectedPage.class) method.

In this case code should look like:

final PolicyPage pp = Navigation.loginToAdminSuite(getWebDriver());

final ConfigStudioPage csp = pp.getConfigStudioMenuItem().click(ConfigStudioPage.class));

final CaseTypeMaintenancePage_CaseType ctmp_CaseType = sp.CaseTypesImageButton.click(CaseTypeMaintenancePage_CaseType.class);

