We shouldn&#39;t expose the absence management service from the builder, we should just derive it from the SA.

Something like:

final ServiceDetailsServiceProvided serviceDetailsServiceProvided =
				serviceAgreementWithAbsenceManagementCarrier.getServiceDetails().getServiceDetailsServiceProvideds().get(0);

		final AbsenceManagementService absenceManagementService = (AbsenceManagementService) serviceDetailsServiceProvided;

and go from there.

Use EnumUtils getFilteredEnumInstances to get the appropriate List of longs in this case something like below would return the list you are looking for
Also this helps to remove logic from the widget, as best practice we try and keep business logic out of the widgets, if needed we put the logic in a service we can reference
EnumUtils.getFilteredEnumInstances(LeavePlanStatus.DOMAIN_ID, LeavePlanStatus.SUBSET_COPY_EMPLOYER_LEAVE_PLAN_STATUS, LeavePlanStatus.PLEASE_SELECT);

